cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SD 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to analyze affective reactions in first-person narratives. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves learning patterns from data, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses techniques such as deep learning and neural networks, which are commonly used in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) research. The paper also involves information retrieval and sentiment analysis, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) sub-categories.
